<tbody valign="top"><row rowsep="0"><entry colsep="0" morerows="0" rowsep="0">1.</entry>
<entry align="left" colsep="0" morerows="0" nameend="col5" namest="col2" rowsep="0">Summary note</entry>
</row>
<row rowsep="0"><entry colsep="0" morerows="0" rowsep="0"/>
<entry colsep="0" morerows="0" rowsep="0"/>
<entry align="left" colsep="0" morerows="0" nameend="col5" namest="col3" rowsep="0"><emph typestyle="ib">Division 1 &#x2014; Preliminary &#x2014; Rule 28.1</emph></entry>
</row>
<row rowsep="0"><entry colsep="0" morerows="0" rowsep="0"/>
<entry colsep="0" morerows="0" rowsep="0"/>
<entry colsep="0" morerows="0" rowsep="0"/>
<entry align="justify" colsep="0" morerows="0" nameend="col5" namest="col4" rowsep="0">When read with Division 2, this rule permits orders for separate determination to be made in relation to any matter to be determined in the proceedings.</entry>
</row>
<row rowsep="0"><entry colsep="0" morerows="0" rowsep="0"/>
<entry colsep="0" morerows="0" rowsep="0"/>
<entry align="left" colsep="0" morerows="0" nameend="col5" namest="col3" rowsep="0"><emph typestyle="ib">Division 2 &#x2014; Separation of questions &#x2014; Rules 28.2&#x2013;28.4</emph></entry>
</row>
<row rowsep="0"><entry colsep="0" morerows="0" rowsep="0"/>
<entry colsep="0" morerows="0" rowsep="0"/>
<entry colsep="0" morerows="0" rowsep="0"/>
<entry align="justify" colsep="0" morerows="0" nameend="col5" namest="col4" rowsep="0">These rules permit orders to be made for the separate determination of any question in the proceedings. The rules permit the court to make appropriate orders to give effect to the separately determined question, including orders disposing of the proceedings.</entry>
</row>
<row rowsep="0"><entry colsep="0" morerows="0" rowsep="0"/>
<entry colsep="0" morerows="0" rowsep="0"/>
<entry align="left" colsep="0" morerows="0" nameend="col5" namest="col3" rowsep="0"><emph typestyle="ib">Division 3 &#x2014; Consolidation and linking of proceedings &#x2014; Rule 28.5</emph></entry>
</row>
<row rowsep="0"><entry colsep="0" morerows="0" rowsep="0"/>
<entry colsep="0" morerows="0" rowsep="0"/>
<entry colsep="0" morerows="0" rowsep="0"/>
<entry align="justify" colsep="0" morerows="0" nameend="col5" namest="col4" rowsep="0">This rule permits consolidation, or the related hearing, of proceedings and particularly those involving common questions, or rights arising out of related transactions.</entry>
</row>
<row rowsep="0"><entry colsep="0" morerows="0" rowsep="0">2.</entry>
<entry align="left" colsep="0" morerows="0" nameend="col5" namest="col2" rowsep="0">Application</entry>
</row>
<row rowsep="0"><entry colsep="0" morerows="0" rowsep="0"/>
<entry align="justify" colsep="0" morerows="0" nameend="col5" namest="col2" rowsep="0">This Part applies to all courts in Schedule 1 of the CP Act, except in relation to proceedings in the Local Court, Small Claims Division: see r 1.5 and Sch 1.</entry>
</row>
<row rowsep="0"><entry colsep="0" morerows="0" rowsep="0">3.</entry>
<entry align="left" colsep="0" morerows="0" nameend="col5" namest="col2" rowsep="0">Historical note</entry>
</row>
<row rowsep="0"><entry colsep="0" morerows="0" rowsep="0"/>
<entry align="justify" colsep="0" morerows="0" nameend="col5" namest="col2" rowsep="0">The Part substantially reproduces the terms of the former SCR Part 31 and DCR Part 12.</entry>
</row>
</tbody>
</tgroup>
</table>
</p>
